Subject:
Your identity could not be confirmed for GOV.UK One Login

Message:
Dear ((first name)) ((last name)),

You recently went to a Post Office to prove your identity with GOV.UK One Login.

There was a problem and we could not confirm your identity.

You can try to prove your identity again to access the service you need to use. 

1. Go to GOV.UK
2. Search for ‘Services you can use with GOV.UK One Login’
3. Select ‘Services you can use with GOV.UK One Login’
4. Select the service you need to use from the list
5. When prompted, sign in with GOV.UK One Login
6. You’ll then be asked to try proving your identity again

Regards,

GOV.UK One Login team